Practice Questions:

1. Find services that have admitted more than 500 patients in total.
select service, count(*) as total_admitted from patients group by service having count(*) >=500; 

2. Show services where average patient satisfaction is below 75.
select service, avg(satisfaction) as Avg_satisfaction from patients group by service having avg(satisfaction) <75;

3. List weeks where total staff presence across all services was less than 50.
select week, count(*) as total_staff from services_weekly group by week having count(*) <50;

### Daily Challenge:

**Question:**
Identify services that refused more than 100 patients in total and had an average patient satisfaction below 80. Show service name, total refused, and average satisfaction.

SELECT 
    service,
    SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Refused' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_refused,
    AVG(satisfaction) AS avg_satisfaction
FROM patients
GROUP BY service
HAVING 
    SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Refused' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > 100
    AND AVG(satisfaction) < 80;











